Dear 12th grade Students and Parents,
You’re invited to EducationQuest Foundation’s Virtual Financial Aid Program. By attending, you’ll learn how to pay for college and will be eligible to register for a $500 scholarship!

Date and Time: 8/31 at 6:00 PM
Topic: EducationQuest’s Financial Aid Program
Time: Aug. 31, 2020 06:00 PM Central Time (US and Canada)
Join Zoom Meeting
https://educationquest-org.zoom.us/j/91612730142?pwd=L2dML3J1M0drK0RNSVlCaXh0V0xxdz09
Meeting ID: 916 1273 0142
Passcode: 779234

As you participate in the presentation, you may want to reference these resources:
Presentation Slides
Create a Federal Student Aid Account Handout
FAFSA Checklist
Scholarship Tip Sheet
Tuition Assistance Handout
Junior/Senior Timeline
If you need help with college planning or the FAFSA, call EducationQuest to set up a free virtual appointment.

Other Resources:
To stay on track to college, sign up for the Countdown2College email service and attend the EducationQuest Virtual College Fair September 27-30.

Contact Mr. Nixon if you have any questions!

post_text:
WELCOME BACK PENDRAGONS!!!

It is SOOOOOOO good to see everyone! Today is the start of a great school year!
text:
WELCOME BACK PENDRAGONS!!!

It is SOOOOOOO good to see everyone! Today is the start of a great school year!

post_text:
Good evening,

Today is the last day of the summer break, which means the 2020-2021 school year starts TOMORROW!! Hopefully students are excited to come back, because PPS staff members are thrilled for them to be back! It has been WAY too long since school was last in session, and everyone at the school is very excited to get the school year started!

Here are a few reminders…

1. School will be dismissed tomorrow at 1:00 pm

2. Please do NOT arrive before 8:00 am.

3. Breakfast will be grab and go and will be eaten in the classrooms.

4. Facial coverings will be required. If you have one, please put it on before entering the building. If you do not have one, one will be available when you arrive!

Again, everyone at PPS looks forward to seeing you and can’t wait to get the school year started!

See you all tomorrow and have a great evening!

Its a Great Day to be a Pendragon!!

PPS Mask/Facial Covering Protocol for Students and Staff:
* Put your mask/facial covering on as you exit your car (or when you arrive on school grounds if you are walking or riding a bike).
*If you don't have a mask/facial covering they will be available for you outside door 4 (main entrance).
*Masks/facial coverings will be worn while waiting outside to enter the building.
*Masks/facial coverings will be worn inside the building when appropriate social distancing is not possible.
Practice wearing those masks! Let's all work together to keep our kids in school! #8moredays

Nebraska 4-H
June 5 at 11:02 AM ·

The Online Horticulture Judging Contest is now open! 🌿 Test your horticulture knowledge: 4h.unl.edu/online-horticulture-judging-contest

The Online Horticulture Judging Contest provides youth an opportunity to test their knowledge of growing fruits, vegetables, flowers, and ornamental plants. The contest is open to all youth, as well as adults. Youth do not need to be enrolled 4-H members to participate. The contest will be available from 8:00 AM on Friday, June 5, 2020, through 8:00 AM on Monday, June 22, 2020.

Nebraska 4-H
June 5 at 2:01 PM ·

The NEW Online Insect Identification Contest is now open! 🐞Test your insect knowledge: 4h.unl.edu/online-insect-id-contest

The Online Insect Identification Contest provides an opportunity for participants to put their entomological knowledge to the test. The contest consists of insect identification and multiple-choice questions. The contest is open to all youth, as well as adults. Youth do not need to be enrolled 4-H members to participate. The contest will be available from Friday, June 5 through Friday, June 19, 2020.

post_text: Summer is in full swing and so is our Summer Meals Program. During the month of May, We served 4238 Breakfasts, and 4238 Lunches. That is 8476 Total Meals! That is A LOT of food. The BEST part is that it is FREE! Any child ages 1-18 can eat FREE! Call the school anytime to sign up or you can email schoolsmeals@penderschools.org. We also deliver to children that are on our bus routes. Don't miss out!

post_text: We will open our final Find It Friday search to the public! Entries due by this Friday, May 15th. See the details below!
shared_text:
Pender Public Schools
May 8 at 6:59 PM ·

Find It Friday- Round #3

Round #2 winner was Chloe Lortz! Congratulations your pizza gift certificate will be ready for pick up in the office Monday!

Welcome to our third and final "Find It Friday" challenge - barn quilt edition! Take a walk or a cruise around Pender (using appropriate social distance and following CDC guidelines of course) and see if you can figure out the locations shown in these 22 pictures! Once you have identified all 22 locations, email your answers to finditfriday@penderschools.org! Entries are due by Sunday, May 10th @ 10:00 p.m. The PPS student with the most correct answers will win a gift certificate for a large Welsh's Pizza! If there is a tie, the earliest entry will win. All locations are able to be seen from a vehicle within city limits. Each photo is numbered. Good Luck Pendragons!!

post_text:
Find It Friday- Round #2

Round #1 winner was Max & Corrine Kinning! Congratulations your pizza gift certificate is ready for pick up in the office!

Welcome to our second "Find It Friday" challenge - business edition! Take a walk or a cruise around Pender (using appropriate social distance and following CDC guidelines of course) and see if you can figure out the locations shown in these 20 pictures! Once you have identified all 20 locations, email your answers to finditfriday@penderschools.org! Entries are due by Sunday, April 26th @ 10:00 p.m. The PPS student with the most correct answers will win a gift certificate for a large Welsh's Pizza! If there is a tie, the earliest entry will win. All locations are able to be seen from a vehicle within city limits. Each photo is numbered. We will have a new Find It Friday Challenge next week! Good Luck Pendragons!!
